                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d2">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15A4 Steering Committee/507: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-04-14T17:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 14, 1937—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>25. Your letter of April 6 to Dunn.<note n="2" xml:id="d2fn2">James C. Dunn,
                        Chief of the Division of Western European Affairs; letter not found in
                        Department files.</note> We would like to have your views on Norman
                        Davis’<note n="3" xml:id="d2fn3">Chairman of the American delegation,
                        Conference for the Reduction and Limitation of Armaments, Geneva; Mr. Davis
                        was in London as Chairman of the American delegation to the International
                        Sugar Conference (see <ref target="#pg_931">pp. 931</ref> ff.)</note>
                    proceeding to Geneva for meeting of Disarmament Bureau May 6. Decision has been
                    left to Mr. Davis. While this Government has no desire to take any initiative at
                    Bureau meeting, we do not desire that any impression should be given of any lack
                    of interest on our part in the question.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
